            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "An ore louse's Strikes causes metal to rapidly rust and corrode. If it succeeds at a mandibles or oxidizing spit Strike, the ore louse deals 3d6 damage (or double damage on a critical hit) to a metal item the target is wearing or holding, ignoring its Hardness. If the ore louse hits an unattended metal item, the item takes this damage automatically. If a creature uses the Shield Block reaction with a metal shield against the attacks, the shield is automatically broken, but no other item is rusted on that attack.",
